==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dibranchiata
<hw>Di*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ gills.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of cephalopods which includes those
with two gills, an apparatus for emitting an inky fluid, and either
eight or ten cephalic arms bearing suckers or hooks, as the octopi and
squids. See <er>Cephalopoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dibranchiate</ent>⟦br⟧
